    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"fleeting beauty\" is just a nice way of saying it's all temporary and ultimately hollow. if there's no point to any of it, and we're just suffering through this tiny window of time before we disappear forever, why is anyone even trying to find \"appreciation\" in it? it feels more like we're just being cruel to ourselves by pretending it matters.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
